  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="Aink6-kilavi">
        <p type="edition"> kaḷaviṉiṟ palanāḷoḻuki (C3: palaṉāḷoḻuki; G2-c: palanāḷoḻuku) vantu
          varaintukoṇṭa (TT, C3, G2-c: uraintukoṇṭa) talaimakaṉ tōḻiyōṭu (VP: tōḻiyoṭu) collāṭi,
          ‘yāṉ varaiyātu (G2-c: varaiyā) oḻukukiṉṟa (G2-c: __ḻukiṉṟa) nāḷ nīyir iṅku iḻaittirunta
          (TT, C3, C4, CX-1, G1: nīyir ninaittirunta; G2-c: ____tirunta) tiṟam yātu?’ eṉṟāṟku avaḷ
          colliyatu. </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en"> </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="Aink6">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> vāḻi yātaṉ vāḻi yaviṉi</l>
          <l> vēntupakai taṇika yāṇṭupala nantuka</l>
          <l> veṉavēṭ ṭōḷē yāyē yāmē</l>
          <l> malarnta poykai mukainta tāmarait</l>
          <l> taṇṭuṟai yūraṉ varaika</l>
          <l> ventaiyuṅ koṭukka veṉavēṭ ṭēmē.</l>
        </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l> “May Ātaṉ prosper, may Aviṉi prosper.</l>
          <l> May the king’s enemies calm down, may he flourish for many years”,</l>
          <l> thus wants our mother. We,</l>
          <l> “let the man from the village by the cool ghat with lotuses</l>
          <l> that budded in the blooming pond propose marriage,</l>
          <l> and let our father give [me]”, thus we want.</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
